Some examples of bug reports writed by me. 1st - UI bug, 2nd - Functional bug, 3rd - Logic bug, 4th - Perfomance bug, 5th - User Expiernce bug 

#1
Title: In the Login page input fields are not center alighned
Steps to reproduce:
  1. Open the link
  2. Open the DevTools
  3. Hover mouse over input fields "Username" and "Password"
  4. In the Styles tab inside of DevTools, check padding for these fields
Actual result: Left padding is 0px, which looks unbalanced 
Expected result: Field "Username" and "Password" should be vertically and horizontally alighned 
Severity: Low
Priority: Low
Attachment: Screenshot/videorecording attached

#2
!!!Title: Error message does not fit the expected area
Steps to reproduce:
1.Open the link
2. Fill the username field with data "secret_sauce"
3. Fill the password field with data "standard_user"
4. Click on "Login"
Actual result: Error message for wrong login credentials goes beyoung the borders
Expected result: Error message should stay within its container
Severity: Medium
Priority: Medium
Attachment: Screenshot/videorecording attached

#3
!!!Title: Toggle password visibility is missing 
Steps to reproduce:
  1. Open the link
  2. Fill the password field with the data "secret_sauce"
Actual result: User is unable to check the spelling of the password
Expected result: There should be an eye icon inside of password field, that allows the user to toggle password visibility 
Severity: Low
Priority: Medium
Attachment: Screenshot/videorecording attached

